Package gw.cc.catastrophe.entity

Interface Catastrophe

All Superinterfaces:
ZoneContainer
public interface Catastrophe extends ZoneContainer
Catastrophe Represents a catastrophe to code claims with. Each catastrophe has a unique name and catastrophe number.

  • Method Details

    • getRelevantZoneTypesForCountry

      List<ZoneType> getRelevantZoneTypesForCountry(Country country)
      Returns all the zone types relevant to catastrophes for the given country. This is used to decide which zone types to show in the catastrophe UI for building catastrophe zones, and hence determines which types of zone can be built using the UI.

      The current implementation returns all the zone types that have a "granularity" specified in the zone-config.xml file, in reverse granularity order (i.e. least specific first)

      Parameters:
      country - a non null country for which we need zone types
      Returns:
      a non null list of zone types

    • getZoneList

      List getZoneList()
      Returns an alphabetized arraylist of the zones covered by the given catastrophe. Zones are represented as strings. Strips leading and trailing whitespace.
      Returns:
      a list of zones

    • getZones

      String getZones()
      Returns an alphabetized arraylist of the zones covered by the given catastrophe. Zones are represented as strings. Strips leading and trailing whitespace.
      Returns:
      a comma-separated list of zones

    • containsZone

      boolean containsZone(Country country, ZoneType zoneType, String zone)
      Checks if this catastrophe contains a zone of the given type and value. The string matching is case-insensitive NOTE: this will not match if a zip+4 value is provided. You must strip off the +4 before passing to this method.
      Parameters:
      zoneType - the zone type, must not be null
      zone - the zone string, must not be null
      Returns:
      true if the region containsZone a zone of the given type, false otherwise

    • addCatastropheZoneFilter

      Query<Claim> addCatastropheZoneFilter(Query<Claim> query)
      Returns a Query that is like the passed-in query but performs the relevant filtering in the database for finding claims with a loss location matching the current catastrophes zones. Can return the original Query with modifications or null (indicates that the filtered Query would return no data).
